The Vice President, Kamala Harris, gave a speech at the Carpenters International Training Center in Las Vegas, Nevada. She spoke about the importance of labor unions and the role they played in helping people achieve their potential. Harris also discussed the need for infrastructure investment and the bipartisan Infrastructure Framework that would create jobs for carpenters and other workers. She urged the audience to support vaccination efforts to combat COVID-19 and emphasized the importance of solidarity and looking out for one another. Harris ended her speech by celebrating the resilience and kindness of the American people and wishing everyone a happy Fourth of July.